OL,5,FInitially, the fraudsters were simply
OL,6,Ftaking people's money and leaving the
OL,7,Fcustomers with nothing to show for it,
OL,8,Fleading to complaints being directed
OL,9,Fback to Martha.
OL,11,FBut then things took an unexpected
OL,12,Fturn. Using images of the calendar
OL,13,Ffrom the internet, the fraudsters had
OL,14,Fproduced their own low-quality copy of
OL,15,FMartha's product. Customers began
OL,16,Freceiving the low-quality counterfeit
OL,17,Fcalendar, and complaints followed.
